n\nthresholds given different datasets on one full orbit. In particular, with a\nfull orbit of data of 50 microarcseconds (VLTI/GRAVITY) and 10 km/s\n(VLT/SINFONI) precision, the 1{\\sigma} bound would improve to about 1000 solar\nmasses, for example.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 14 Dec 2021 22:57:09 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-04-20"}
